<item>
            <title>[LU-6048] Kernel update [RHEL7 3.10.0-123.13.2.el7]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6048</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A flaw was found in the way the Linux kernel handled GS segment register&lt;br/&gt;
base switching when recovering from a #SS (stack segment) fault on an&lt;br/&gt;
erroneous return to user space. A local, unprivileged user could use this&lt;br/&gt;
flaw to escalate their privileges on the system. (CVE-2014-9322, Important)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Bugs fixed (&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugzilla.redhat.com/):&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugzilla.redhat.com/):&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1172806 - CVE-2014-9322 kernel: x86: local privesc due to bad_iret and paranoid entry incompatibility&lt;/p&gt;</description>
